  "text": "The adenosine triphosphate (ATP) from spermatozoa cells was determined using the ViaLight Plus kit according to the manufacturer's instructions (Cambrex Bio Science Rockland, Inc., USA) [CITATION_1] . Prior to assay, samples composed of 10 μL of diluted semen were mixed with 100 μL Cell Lysis Reagent and incubated at room temperature for 5 minutes to extract ATP from cells. Following the addition of 100 μL ATP Monitoring Reagent via automated dispensers, luminescence was measured using an AutoLumat LB953 luminometer (Berthold, Bad Wildbad, Germany). Sperm ATP content from each probe was assessed in duplicate.",
